The paper discusses the use of mobile robots for safety, security, and rescue applications, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also focuses on the problem of resilient design against system-wide failures and attacks, which is related to multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper mentions denial-of-service attacks, which is a type of security threat, and thus the paper may also belong to the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm for solving a resilient design problem, which involves optimization and approximation, and thus may also belong to the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
